oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Proceedings of the Twentieth Annual Conference (1987). Social Events and Annual Membership Luncheon Meeting
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Bovine Practitioners, American Association of
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: America celebrated her 200th anniversary of the signing of the Constitution. It was indeed, a fitting coincidence that the AABP would celebrate its 20th Annual Conference under the presidency of Dr. George E. Washington. To add elegance to the occasion, the President and his lovely wife, Patti, appeared at the pre-convention fiesta on Tuesday evening dressed in true Presidential Washington era style. The Annual Membership Luncheon Meeting was held on Friday, November 13. Dr. George Washington presided and gave the invocation. The minutes of the November 21, 1986, meeting were approved as published in the December 1986 newsletter.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: American Association of Bovine Practitioners Conference Proceedings; 1987; vii-xi
